			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>
				<date>Novr 24<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1859</date></p>
			<p>My Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I beg you will pardon my seeming neglect<lb/> in not writing you at an earlier date
				but the truth<lb/> is I have been so busily occupied of late that I have<lb/> not
				had scarce a moments leisure time&#59; this day<lb/> being <date>Thanksgiving
					Day</date>&#44; and the Courts and lawyers&#39;<lb/> offices being closed&#44; I
				have determined to devote the best<lb/> portion of it to my correspondents some of
				whose letters I<lb/> have unanswered for nearly a year.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I therefore begin with the most esteemed&#8212;yourself&#44; my<lb/> dear and much
				respected friend.</p>
			<p>I sent you a printed report of the decision &#38;c in your suite<lb/> against
					<persName>Frank</persName> and <persName>Sklarz</persName> and on the
						<date>17<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> inst<lb/> a package by Adams Express
				containing five copies of<lb/> the printed edition of your Pentateuch.</p>
			<p>We have settled now with all but <persName>Sklarz</persName>&#44; and I<lb/> am
				satisfied <hi rend="underline">he</hi> has not ten dollars which could be<lb/>
				collected of him by way of damages&#44; or costs.</p>
			<p>Against each and all of them injunctions had to be<lb/> obtained and have been
				obtained.</p>
			<p>With <persName>Ottinger</persName>&#44; as you are already aware&#44; we settled for
				&#36;100<lb/> cash. With <persName>Ettinger</persName> &#38;
					<persName>Gotthold</persName>&#8212;as you advised&#8212;<lb/> &#36;50 in
				cash&#44; and their note at 6 months for &#36;50. &#38; forfeit the books<lb/>
				<persName>Frank</persName> could pay but &#36;32.50 &#40;he is out of business
				now&#41;<lb/> and <persName>Sklarz</persName> has not paid and cannot pay
				anything</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
			<p>Here then you have a statement of the disbursements<lb/> which have necessarily been
				made&#58;</p>
